         <h2>Join as an Exchange Participant</h2>
		 <p>
		 Want to go abroad through AIESEC, but don't have the time to dedicate to joining our organization?  Not a
		 problem, just join as an Exchange Participant.  We will set you up on our world-wide database of internships
		 and help you through the whole process of finding and realizing the best internship for you.
		 </p>
		 <a href = "joinep.php" style = "float: right;">Find out more</a>
		 <br>
		 <h2>Join our student organization</h2>
	     <p>
	     As a member of AIESEC Michigan, you will have full access to the opportunities that AIESEC brings.  You might
		 network with local businesses in need of international talent, help students at Michigan find their
		 dream job abroad, or just show our foreign interns a good time in their new home in Michigan.  You'll be able
		 to make personal contacts with local companies, faculty and staff of the university, and other students like
		 you from all over the world, all while working and hanging out with our over 50 other internationally focused 
		 members.  And of course, you'll also be set up on our world-wide internship database and have the full
		 opportunity to go abroad!
		 </p>
		 <a href = "joinlc.php" style = "float: right;">Find out more</a>
		 <br>
		 <h2>The application process</h2>
		 <p>
		 Know whether you want to apply to become a full member, or just to go abroad as an Exchange Participant?  Then
		 download and complete the application below, then email it to
		 <a href = "mailto: aiesecmichigan@gmail.com">aiesec.recruit@gmail.com</a>
		 before the deadline.  If you're selected for an interview, we will let you know your interview time and date
		 within about a week of the deadline.  After this, we will email you again in about a week with our final
		 decisions.
		 </p>
		 <p>
		 We generally recruit at least once per semester, so check our
		 Announcements section or our 
		 <a href = "calendar.php">Calendar</a>
		 in the bar on the left 
		 for upcoming deadlines.  We also hold several info sessions before each recruitment, and we highly encourage
		 members to attend, ask questions, and find out first hand what AIESEC is all about.
		 </p>
		 <br>
